{"credits": [], "cve_id": "CVE-2026-40048", "cvss": {"score": 7.8, "vector_string": "CVSS:3.1/AV:L/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:H/A:H"}, "cvss_severities": {"cvss_v3": {"score": 7.8, "vector_string": "CVSS:3.1/AV:L/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:H/A:H"}, "cvss_v4": {"score": 0.0, "vector_string": null}}, "cwes": [{"cwe_id": "CWE-502", "name": "Deserialization of Untrusted Data"}], "description": "The Camel-PQC FileBasedKeyLifecycleManager class deserializes the contents of `<keyId>.key` files in the configured key directory using java.io.ObjectInputStream without applying any ObjectInputFilter or class-loading restrictions. The cast to `java.security.KeyPair` is evaluated only after `readObject()` has already returned, so any `readObject()` side effects in the deserialized object run before the type check. An attacker who can write to the key directory used by a Camel application — for example through a path traversal into the directory, misconfigured filesystem permissions on the volume where keys are stored, a compromised key provisioning pipeline, or a symlink attack — can place a crafted serialized Java object that, when deserialized during normal key lifecycle operations, results in arbitrary code execution in the context of the application.

This issue affects Apache Camel: from 4.19.0 before 4.20.0, from 4.18.0 before 4.18.2.

Users are recommended to upgrade to version 4.20.0, which fixes the issue by replacing java.io.ObjectInputStream-based key and metadata storage with standard PKCS#8 (private key) / X.509 SubjectPublicKeyInfo (public key) Base64 JSON encoding. For users on the 4.18.x LTS releases stream, upgrade to 4.18.2.", "epss": {"percentage": 0.00342, "percentile": 0.26006}, "ghsa_id": "GHSA-v3vg-332r-mw99", "github_reviewed_at": "2026-05-05T21:18:38Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/advisories/GHSA-v3vg-332r-mw99", "identifiers": [{"type": "GHSA", "value": "GHSA-v3vg-332r-mw99"}, {"type": "CVE", "value": "CVE-2026-40048"}], "nvd_published_at": "2026-04-27T09:16:01Z", "published_at": "2026-04-27T09:34:38Z", "references": ["https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2026-40048", "https://camel.apache.org/security/CVE-2026-40048.html", "http://www.openwall.com/lists/oss-security/2026/04/26/6", "https://github.com/apache/camel/pull/22034", "https://github.com/apache/camel/pull/22495", "https://github.com/apache/camel/commit/5bdd0f1d3289dfa78116deec6c81083708bf432d", "https://github.com/apache/camel/commit/5f87a86f4e337efc59248d278c6a5650e73b3b7c", "https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-23200", "https://github.com/advisories/GHSA-v3vg-332r-mw99"], "repository_advisory_url": null, "severity": "high", "source_code_location": "https://github.com/apache/camel", "summary": "Camel-PQC Vulnerable to Deserialization of Untrusted Data", "type": "reviewed", "updated_at": "2026-05-05T21:18:39Z", "url": "https://api.github.com/advisories/GHSA-v3vg-332r-mw99", "vulnerabilities": [{"first_patched_version": "4.18.2", "package": {"ecosystem": "maven", "name": "org.apache.camel:camel-pqc"}, "vulnerable_functions": [], "vulnerable_version_range": "< 4.18.2"}], "withdrawn_at": null}
